</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7FBC3ABDD2A98958323CB9472672C3E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="notes">
<paragraph id="AEF782DEB58898CA6F1DE4929CAF56E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA41ED86BC9336016A5B7D5445579BBE" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Morphologically, the present isolate resembles 
<taxonomicName id="64E28E65B9C53473A5A56E49E93F4231" class="Entomophthoromycetes" family="Dalceridae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ca. denaeosporum" order="Entomophthorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Entomophthoromycota" rank="species" species="denaeosporum">
<emphasis id="EC33C7D2CD990837D1E0CDE09E3C32F8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Ca. denaeosporum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the size of its primary conidia (13-32 
<normalizedToken id="1882CFD649821AF234004ED8FD2A2E8E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-21 
<normalizedToken id="26879EDBAD40AE71D518C1211334A7A6" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="0A899C34A18104CCFA021CD2125DBA17" class="Entomophthoromycetes" family="Dalceridae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ca. denaeosporum" order="Entomophthorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Entomophthoromycota" rank="species" species="denaeosporum">
<emphasis id="32DAB94BB713A21964138BD28310D8D9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Ca. denaeosporum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 21-31 
<normalizedToken id="16E12E160180327AAA326B9C800B6222" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12-29 
<normalizedToken id="2BA44CD6C0691F397916A1AEA440BE4D" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="6356BC7A3F14890062882F043B4C39CA" class="Entomophthoromycetes" family="Dalceridae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ca. jiangsuense" order="Entomophthorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Entomophthoromycota" rank="species" species="jiangsuense">
<emphasis id="F0EEAB8690DDBE904A56D124AC10E9DA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Ca. jiangsuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="5F2B9F69FCC3986ED2037998F2F7F3A7" author="Drechsler, C" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="309 - 315" refId="B12" refString="Drechsler, C, 1957. Two medium-sized species of Conidiobolus occurring in Colorado. Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences 47: 309 - 315" title="Two medium-sized species of Conidiobolus occurring in Colorado." volume="47" year="1957">Drechsler 1957</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="05442A3E968778FC4F2EDC872D756724" class="Entomophthoromycetes" family="Dalceridae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ca. denaeosporum" order="Entomophthorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Entomophthoromycota" rank="species" species="denaeosporum">
<emphasis id="4008A1EE1B2DF3D51CBA9376D35122C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Ca. denaeosporum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has larger capilliconidia (10-18 
<normalizedToken id="6D908615055395DBC17B43DFE07AB320" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-10 
<normalizedToken id="40892CA699935C4023BB7F059044EDB3" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="F0DFF6D65A48F10FCE35A9FDA1508A26" class="Entomophthoromycetes" family="Dalceridae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ca. denaeosporum" order="Entomophthorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Entomophthoromycota" rank="species" species="denaeosporum">
<emphasis id="C47490B8FD371358027F1AD9BCD8388C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Ca. denaeosporum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 17-32 
<normalizedToken id="A71152CD5AAB01E15F6F5DD205FFB9B2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10-15 
<normalizedToken id="228FCDF36BE184C5C0B15017D8105D32" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="7912208974191822BA42E22A1093F04A" class="Entomophthoromycetes" family="Dalceridae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ca. jiangsuense" order="Entomophthorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Entomophthoromycota" rank="species" species="jiangsuense">
<emphasis id="3D6DE27D1F9FDCF38D30F2A843D69456" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Ca. jiangsuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and longer, more slender secondary conidiophores (35-65 
<normalizedToken id="623AF68D237E0E931B290E82F1B1A7BD" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="E748C7C27804914B7E27EB205E5F2502" class="Entomophthoromycetes" family="Dalceridae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ca. denaeosporum" order="Entomophthorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Entomophthoromycota" rank="species" species="denaeosporum">
